[SourceTitle "01 Introduction"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "gm-avrukh-against-the-scotch-game/course/5884, variation/230038"]

{Boris Avrukh is a GM originating from Israel, who reached a peak rating of 2668 in 
2009. While Boris is a serious chess competitor, a former under-12 World Champion and 
twice Israel Champion, he is also a great chess author. On a personal note, I 
discovered Boris’ work through his great Slav Repertoire book, which taught me as 
much about the middle-game that it did about the opening. It is the quality of that 
work which led me to reach out to Boris for our first work for Chessable. The 
analysis that follows is almost entirely Boris’s. In the rare cases where an 
additional line needed mentioning, I have included my initials (JS) in the comments. 
I hope you will enjoy this opening repertoire as much as I liked editing it. Jerome 
Solakian, London 2017.} 1. -- *

