1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5 5. Nb3 Bb6 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Qe2 O-O 8. Be3 d5 
$1 {It took me some time to realize, but this move is essential. Without this break 
Black has a very passive position.} 9. O-O-O d4 $1 {And this is the key follow-up. 
The pin along d-file look annoying, but Black has everything in order..} 10. Na4 $6 
{seems logical, threatening the Bishop supporting the d4 pawn, but is dubious due to} 
Qe8 $1 {a move with beautiful geometry! Black unpins the d4 pawn so the Be3 is now en 
prise. At the same time, the Black Queen eyes the Na4 through the Nc6, so as to force 
White to capture on b6 before taking on d4. This in turn allows Black to recapture on 
b6 with the a-pawn, after which... Ra2 becomes possible.} 11. Nxb6 axb6 12. Bxd4 Nxd4 
13. Rxd4 c5 $1 14. Rd1 Rxa2 15. Kb1 Qa4 $19 *

