[Comment "gm-avrukh-against-the-scotch-game/course/5884, variation/230128"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5 5. Be3 Qf6 6. c3 Nge7 7. Bc4 O-O 8. O-O b6 
{This move is played less often than the alternatives, but scores very well for 
Black. 8... b6 is a good multi-purpose move, which protects the c5-bishop and allows 
the light square bishop to develop on b7 or even on a6, as we will see in some of the 
lines that follow. Now I checked four possibilities for White:} 9. Qd2 Qg6 10. Nxc6 
Qxc6 11. Bxc5 Qxc5 12. Na3 a5 $1 13. Rfe1 d6 14. Bf1 Bd7 $146 15. Nc2 Rfe8 16. Nd4 b5 
{with a very reliable position.} *

